We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

Enforce immediate relief of Rizza B. Gonzales from her present assignment as Special Collecting Officer to prevent her from incurring further shortage and to avoid manipulation of records;

Require explanation from the Municipal Treasurer why he could not be charged administratively for dereliction of duty:

For allowing Rizza B. Gonzales to use several stubs of accountable forms (AF No. 56) which she issued simultaneously in collecting Real Property Taxes (RPT); 

Failure to closely supervise and enforce daily turnover and remittance of collections and verification of accountable forms, which give her wide opportunity to misappropriate the funds in her custody;  

Failure to establish the required cash management mechanisms and controls to safeguard cash against loss or misappropriations; and 

File administrative and criminal charges against Rizza B. Gonzales pursuant to Article 217 of the Revised Penal Code.

