We recommended that the Municipal Mayor – 
Enforce the mandatory segregation of solid wastes at source pursuant to Section 21 and 22 of RA No. 9003;
Direct all Punong Barangay for the mandatory establishment of MRF in  their respective barangays in consonance with Section 32 of RA No. 9003;
Call the attention of the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board to review annually the “Ten-Year MSWM Plan” of the Municipality pursuant to the requirement of the OIC Executive Director, NSWMC Secretariat, in his letter dated February 27, 2015;
Coordinate or secure an agreement with another LGU with an existing SLF to dispose its residual wastes if construction of a sanitary landfill could not be implemented; and
Implement source reduction, recycling and composting programs through waste diversion activities pursuant to Section 20 of RA No. 9003 to reduce the volume of solid wastes.

